-- Ukraine’s President Wants Pension Tax for Electronic Exchange
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a   a n d   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2013-03-19T12:23:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-19/ukraine-s-president-wants-pension-tax-for-electronic-exchange.html
Ukrainian President  Viktor Yanukovych  wants parliament to vote on a tax on electronic
purchases of foreign currency by companies to raise money for
the pension system.  Yanukovych wants Mykola Azarov’s government to prepare a
bill on the tax for the legislature by April, according to a
March 12 presidential decree published on his official website
late yesterday.  To contact the reporters on this story:
